title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J Kaiser Convention Center on 1987-03-02
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2016
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Althea, CC Rider, Bird Song, Beat It On Down The Line, Ramble On Rose, Feel Like A Stranger

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Jam-> Truckin'-> Morning Dew, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
so happy 4 this For years I posted having to want an aud copy. Thank you thank you thank. Listening to the jam before Truckin and sounds like the Kaiser with that mellow only us tour heads feel and sound.    Thanks so very much for posting this show. I certainly know it's not posted for me but truly glad you posted it.   
sounds good so far
Listened to this one threw out now. You my friend did an outstanding job on this recording. 
May not be 5 stars to others but sure is to me... Having been to every Kaiser show from 85 threw 89 they always had the feeling of local friends gathering for a party.

LAME you actually listed Finiculi Finicula as a song in the set list?
L A M E

Best Aud for this show I’m a little annoyed by the one review here complaining about the crowd singing being a separate track and giving it one star for that alone. The other aud recordings have this too, and it’s preferably normal to have opening/tuning/crowd separated. 
All that said, this one has the cleanest vocals and guitars sound full, you can hear cymbals crashing, it’s almost like a sound board but warmer. Nice work.
